tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE data_cleaning_tasks (
    task_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    task_name VARCHAR(255),
    task_description TEXT,
    task_status ENUM('pending', 'completed'),
    created_at TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE data_preprocessing_steps (
    step_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    step_name VARCHAR(255),
    step_description TEXT,
    step_status ENUM('active', 'inactive'),
    created_at TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE preprocessing_logs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    step_id INT,
    log_message TEXT,
    log_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (step_id) REFERENCES data_preprocessing_steps(step_id)
)

CREATE TABLE data_cleaning_tasks (
    task_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    task_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    task_description TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE process_steps (
    step_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    step_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    step_description TEXT,
    task_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (task_id) REFERENCES data_cleaning_tasks(task_id)
)

CREATE TABLE cleaning_logs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    step_id INT,
    log_message TEXT,
    log_time TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (step_id) REFERENCES process_steps(step_id)
)

CREATE TABLE analysis_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    result_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    result_description TEXT,
    step_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (step_id) REFERENCES process_steps(step_id)
)
